{"name":"Cleaving Spell","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>Your spell with the attack trait kills a creature or knocks it unconscious, and another foe is adjacent to that creature.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Your magic carries on to another foe. Make a spell attack roll against the second foe, applying the spell’s effects accordingly.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"cleaving-spell","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":8},"traits":{"value":["archetype","metamagic"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Aggressive Mage Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.WFKmAqq7ZhxCxvLr"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686113511967,"modifiedTime":1686115188662,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"8I3d5j6N2q1y8caW"}
{"name":"Sneaking Spell","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You can aim your spells at a target’s weak points. Your spells with the attack trait deal an additional 1d4 precision damage to flat-footed creatures. This increases to 1d6 at 6th level and 1d8 at 12th level.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[{"category":"precision","diceNumber":1,"value":{"brackets":[{"end":5,"value":{"dieSize":"d4"}},{"start":6,"end":11,"value":{"dieSize":"d6"}},{"start":12,"value":{"dieSize":"d8"}}]},"key":"DamageDice","predicate":["target:condition:flat-footed"],"selector":"spell-damage"}],"slug":"sneaking-spell","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":4},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Aggressive Mage Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1wFV1FJDmRJIAI6Y"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686113511967,"modifiedTime":1686115187366,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"EbfEJAkJSXKajkmc"}
{"name":"Counter-Counteract","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>One of your non-cantrip spells is counteracted and you can see the creature who made the Counteract check.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Attempt a spell attack roll against the Will DC of the creature that counteracted your spell. On a success, you deal 1d6 mental damage to the target per spell level.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"counter-counteract","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Aggressive Mage Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686113511967,"modifiedTime":1686115188382,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"LDJJURe4730tx5Hv"}
{"name":"Aggressive Mage Dedication","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You pour aggression into your magic. While in this stance, you take a -1 circumstance penalty on your spell DC and to your DCs against spells, and you gain a +1 circumstance bonus on spell attack rolls. You can leave this stance as a single action with the concentrate trait.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.world.magic-specializations-effects.qbnRxiEtJtuBaqnP]{Stance: Aggressive Mage Dedication}</p>\n<p>When you do, you can choose to take two of your metamagic actions from aggressive mage archetype and apply the effects of both to the next spell you cast this turn. You must cast the spell immediately afterwards, as usual.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Special </strong>You can’t select another dedication feat until you’ve gained two other feats from the @UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-magic-journals.6DPJqrJJBdYR5hbz.JournalEntryPage.SKStpLGjr9Hif7Fw]{Aggressive Mage} archetype.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"aggressive-mage-dedication","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":2},"traits":{"value":["archetype","class","dedication","stance"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.83DhElJv0gPIvaWc"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686113511967,"modifiedTime":1686123891180,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"MEQrfPbGICZ9d8yT"}
{"name":"Weighty Spell","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You invest additional potency into your spell. If the next action you use is to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} with the attack trait and no duration, and the spell deals damage, replace any 1s you roll on the damage dice with 2s.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"weighty-spell","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["archetype","fortune","metamagic"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Aggressive Mage Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686113511967,"modifiedTime":1686115113719,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"U5Q1sRQMIVZ1gMPg"}
{"name":"Crackling Spell","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You draw forth additional energy to multiply the damage caused by your spell. If the next action you use is to Cast a Spell with the attack trait that has no duration and deals energy damage (acid, cold, electricity, fire, negative, positive, or sonic) with no splash damage, the spell also deals your choice of @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.lDVqvLKA6eF3Df60]{Persistent Damage} or splash damage of the same type, of an amount equal to the spell’s level.</p>\n<p><strong>Special </strong>When you leave @UUID[Compendium.world.magic-specializations-aggressive-mage.MEQrfPbGICZ9d8yT]{Aggressive Mage Dedication} stance, you can choose to take this metamagic action twice, choosing both persistent damage and splash damage.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"crackling-spell","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":4},"traits":{"value":["archetype","metamagic"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Aggressive Mage Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686113511967,"modifiedTime":1686115179041,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"XFERgGQXwxAS6QYC"}
{"name":"Piercing Spell","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You drive your spell through any obstacles in its way. If the next action you use is to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} with the attack trait, you ignore an amount of the target’s resistance to the damage equal to the spell’s level. Additionally, if the target has a circumstance bonus to the AC that the spell targets, reduce their circumstance bonus by 1.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"piercing-spell","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["archetype","metamagic"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Aggressive Mage Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686113511967,"modifiedTime":1686115113715,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"d0wxTVzeANSUmwLs"}
{"name":"Swiping Spell","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You spread the breadth of your spell. If the next action you use is to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.aBQ8ajvEBByv45yz]{Cast a Spell} with the attack trait that targets a single creature, you instead target two adjacent creatures. Make a single spell attack roll and compare the attack roll result to the AC of the two targets, each of whom must be within the spell’s range.</p>\n<p>Roll damage only once and apply it to each creature you hit. Your spell attack roll counts as two attacks for your multiple attack penalty.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"swiping-spell","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":6},"traits":{"value":["archetype","metamagic"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Aggressive Mage Dedication"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686113511967,"modifiedTime":1686115113717,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"hRQaATG2b4ojCy8y"}
{"name":"Aggressive Magic","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>You’re a spellcaster who specializes in magic that directly attacks your targets. You excel at spells that require an attack roll, but this focus causes your area spells and other effects that require a saving throw to suffer. If you choose this class archetype, you must select the @UUID[Compendium.world.magic-specializations-aggressive-mage.MEQrfPbGICZ9d8yT]{Aggressive Mage Dedication} as your 2nd-level class feat.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> You must be trained in a spell attack roll and a spell DC.</p>\n<p><strong>Aggressive Mage Adjustments</strong>: Your proficiency bonus from being trained in your tradition’s spell DC is only 1 plus your level. For being expert, it’s 3 plus your level; for master, it’s 5 plus your level; and for legendary, it’s 7 plus your level. Your proficiency bonus from being trained in your tradition’s spell attack rolls is 3 plus your level.<br />For being expert, it’s 5 plus your level; for master, it’s 7 plus your level; and for legendary, it’s 9 plus your level.</p>\n<p>If you gain an additional spell slot (such as from a wizard’s school) or an additional spell in your repertoire (such as from a sorcerer’s bloodline), you may choose a common spell with the attack trait instead of the usual restrictions. This spell must come from the same spell list as the one it replaces.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[{"key":"FlatModifier","selector":"spell-attack-roll","value":1},{"key":"FlatModifier","selector":"spell-dc","value":-1}],"slug":"aggressive-magic","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":1},"traits":{"value":[],"rarity":"common"},"category":"classfeature","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"You must be trained in a spell attack roll and a spell DC."}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.X2HuHj3dbes4m3gk"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686113511967,"modifiedTime":1686115158711,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"lS11NG2ghpPd4yTo"}
{"name":"Chaining Spell","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>Your magic carries through multiple foes. When you use @UUID[Compendium.world.magic-specializations-aggressive-mage.8I3d5j6N2q1y8caW]{Cleaving Spell}, if your spell also kills or knocks the target unconscious, you can continue to make spell attack rolls until you make one that doesn’t kill or knock a creature unconscious, or until there are no creatures adjacent to the most recent creature you attacked while using @UUID[Compendium.world.magic-specializations-aggressive-mage.8I3d5j6N2q1y8caW]{Cleaving Spell}, whichever comes first.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"chaining-spell","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":10},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Cleaving Spell"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686113511967,"modifiedTime":1686115170126,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"qIzPUBaUr9arOipR"}
{"name":"Spell Maneuver","type":"feat","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p><strong>Trigger </strong>You succeed at a spell attack roll on a spell with a range of touch.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You use your contact with the target to further harry them. Attempt to @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Disarm]{Disarm}, @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Grapple]{Grapple}, @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Shove]{Shove}, or @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Trip]{Trip} the target. If you critically succeeded on your spell attack roll, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus on the Athletics check.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Frontiers of Magic"},"rules":[],"slug":"spell-maneuver","schema":{"version":0.84,"lastMigration":null},"level":{"value":4},"traits":{"value":["archetype"],"rarity":"common"},"category":"class","onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Aggressive Mage Dedication"},{"value":"expert in Athletics"}]},"location":null},"img":"systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/feat.svg","flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.12.9","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1686113511967,"modifiedTime":1686115187050,"lastModifiedBy":"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Gh9U9I93FE4tnAIO":3},"_id":"wmzmioUhgsKWFATn"}
